Return to School Parent Survey

As USD #462 begins to plan and prepare for the reopening of school in August, we would like to provide parents/guardians of Central Raider students the opportunity to share with the district your thoughts and comments concerning the return to school. We are asking parents/guardians to complete the Return to School Parent Survey which will be open for completion until Wednesday, July 22nd at 10:00 p.m.

https://bit.ly/3iZyksG

We have posted a parent letter that is being mailed out today and uploaded on our website, www.usd462.org in the comments with additional information. We value your input and appreciate your patience as we continue to plan in the coming weeks.

Thank you,
Rick Shaffer
Superintendent

post_text:
Central Raiders Class of 2020 will be graduating tomorrow at 10:00 AM. We will be broadcasting the graduation for the public who cannot attend the ceremony on the Central USD 462 Facebook Live. It will begin airing around 9:50 AM. Thank you and congrats to the 24 seniors who will be crossing the stage tomorrow. #TheRaiderWay!

Thank you to Mr. Shaffer and the USD 462 Board of Education for the approval to go on with the ceremony.

Thank you to Denis and the Summer Maitennace Crew for setting up the Gymnasium.

Thank you to Candace for setting up the technology for the senior video.

Thank you to Leglieter Video for the senior video and the live recording of the ceremony tomorrow.

Thank you to Ms. Powell and Mrs. Miller for your guidance with this Class of 2020 as their class sponsors.

Thank you to Mona for her help in getting sears organized and the diplomas ready.

We look forward to seeing you tomorrow at 8:00 AM Class of 2020.

Saturday, June 20th

Class members ... many of you still need to send Mrs. Miller the following:
1. Photo of you in your cap & gown
2. Senior picture/photo
3. 1 baby picture & 1 other childhood picture
4. Short info about plans after high school
Please get the information turned in by Thursday, May 14th!

Many of you have provided this information, with the exception of the cap & gown photo. If you haven't turned in this information, please send it to either:
amiller@usd462.org
jpowell@usd462.org

This information is what would have been included in our standard commencement video, with the addition of the cap & gown photo. The process of gathering this information had started prior to the events of March. We are attempting to finish obtaining student information to produce a slide show/video that has been a Central tradition.

There will be a Senior Zoom Meeting Monday, May 11th, at 5:00 p.m. A link invitation will be emailed to your school email account in the next couple days. If you have questions prior to that time, please contact Mrs. Miller or Ms. Powell (Class Sponsors) or Mr. Wilson.

post_text: Next week is Teacher Appreciation Week: As teachers are working from home, converting bedrooms, closets, and kitchens into classrooms, I am asking for your help to celebrate our dedicated educators. We know that you, the parents, have been the foundation for your students' success through all of this, and please take the time next week to give yourself a pat on the back as you have all so graciously accepted your current role in education this quarter. We see you, and we thank you too! I appreciate the support and dedication to our students' learning and education, thank you all so very much! Attached is the flyer for this year's Teacher Appreciation Week celebration. Most students can do these things with ease, but some younger students might need your help! I know receiving these videos, emails, and social media posts will fill their teacher hearts! Thank you for choosing to be a light!

post_text:
Calling all Central Raider K-12 Artists!

We know many are sad that we missed our annual Art Show in April. We've heard that many of you are creating some amazing things during your time at home though and we want to celebrate you! To participate, please email Mrs. Henning (jhenning@usd462.org) photos of your artwork by Thursday, April 30th. She will create a virtual art show to distribute during the month of May with anything submitted. Remember, that you don't have to have fancy art supplies at home to get creative. Just follow your heart and express yourself with whatever you can find! Please help us spread the word by sharing this post. Contact Jillian Henning if you have any questions. We can't wait to see your creations!

Dear Families and Community Members:

Our school is hosting a Virtual Scholastic Book Fair from April 13-April 22nd for students of ALL AGES!
The Virtual Fair is a fantastic way to get books in the hands of your students now to keep them reading at home! This opportunity is not just for parents, but family and community members as well. If you wish to purchase for students not in your home, you may shop and add their address at checkout to have the gift of reading delivered to their door!

‚Ä¢ All purchases benefit our school and earn rewards
‚Ä¢ Shop Book Fair exclusives, best-sellers, skill-builders and more
‚Ä¢ Orders ship direct to home
‚Ä¢ Book-only orders over $25* receive FREE shipping
‚Ä¢ Over 6,000 items to choose from through the Scholastic Store Online
Visit our Book Fair Homepage and click ‚ÄúShop Now‚Äù to get started:

https://bookfairs.scholastic.com/bookfairs/cptoolkit/homepage.do?method=homepage&url=centralelementaryschool207

Happy reading!

Lindsay Littrell
Central Elementary Principal

post_text: Join us at 8:20pm (20:20) tonight to light up the night for the Class of 2020. Central Jr./Sr. High will be joining hundreds of schools around the country by turning on our stadium lights to honor the Class of 2020 for 20 minutes. Please enter the west entrance to the field and drive around the parking lot to the softball field and baseball field and then exit back out the west gate. Honk your horns and celebrate the class of 2020. Remember to stay in your cars and practicing social distancing... a must. There will be no congregating during this celebration. Drive in around the lot. and then exit the parking lot. Thank you! #BeTheLight #TheRaiderWay #Classof2020!

Please be advised

Executive Order 20-16 (pg.6, 9b) issued by Governor Laura Kelly today, establishing a statewide ‚Äústay home‚Äù order through April 19, doesn‚Äôt call for any further changes to current K-12 school operations.

Kansas public and private schools will continue to operate under the following guidelines issued by Governor Kelly on March 17, unless prohibited by a district's local county health official.

USD #462 Buildings will be closed the rest of the week except for essential personnel or to perform essential tasks.

Updates on food services and delivery for grab and go lunches will be sent out tomorrow Sunday, March 29.

Our Continuous Learning Plan will start on Monday, March 30.

We will continue to share information as it comes out to us.

Thank you!

USD #462 Administrative Team

post_text: These students participated in the Kansas State concert band clinic January 24-26th in Manhattan. The students auditioned with approx. 1000 others and were placed in one of 7 bands. They put in around 20 hours of playing time including a sunday concert working with directors from KSU, OU, UCF, Texas Tech and Troy among others. They also got to see The Boston Brass perform and work with their groups. Congrats to Tobie Bellew (far right) who was selected for the top band under the direction of K-state director of bands Dr. Frank Tracz.

post_text:
For several years, Central STUCO has had students involved with "Kids Impact Cowley County" (aka KICC) which is supported/sponsored by Southwestern College Leadership & Legacy Foundation. This year, our SWC Leadership students are producing a newsletter, and in the first edition our own Emma Garrison is featured. They made an excellent choice .. her positive attitude, infectious spirit, willingness to lead by example, and work ethic are seen daily at CJSHS. Congrats, Emma!
2019-2020 group also includes: Lane Toon, Angie Price, Mariah Blankenbaker, Sydnie Rosenberger, Morgan Cook, Mallory Bergeron, Casey Gillis, Maddie Brogan.
